author: app.com
title: Local gym owner joins former Navy SEAL's mission
text:
MORE Even by Navy SEAL standards, Andy Stumpf’s mission is ambitious. The Californian is looking to break several skydiving world records and raise $1 million for a good cause in the process.
Across the continent, Manasquan gym owner and strength coach Zach Even-Esh is lending a hand.
As Stumpf prepares to jump out of a plane at 38,000 feet and free-fall for more than nine minutes wearing an aerodynamic “wingsuit,” Even-Esh will be leveraging his big social media following to drum up support, starting with an event this weekend.
Their partnership is shining a light on the Navy SEAL Foundation, which supports wounded SEALs and the families of those who die in the line of duty.
“I’ve probably buried 50 to 60 friends,” said Stumpf, who served in this dangerous occupation for 17 years before retiring for medical reasons.
